<%- include('../partials/layout-start', { pageTitle: 'BWTDallas Portal Hub' }) %>

<header class="page-header hero-header">
  <p class="eyebrow">Bright World Tech operations</p>
  <h1>BWTDallas Portal Hub</h1>
  <p>Create department-specific portals that read from the same MySQL database while showing each team only the views and actions they need.</p>
</header>

<section>
  <h2>Database Snapshot</h2>
  <div class="stats-grid">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <h3>Employees</h3>
      <p><%= summary.employees %></p>
      <span>Total employee records</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <h3>Active Techs</h3>
      <p><%= summary.activeTechnicians %></p>
      <span>Role contains “tech”</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <h3>Units</h3>
      <p><%= summary.units %></p>
      <span>Tracked devices</span>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <h3>Inventory Qty</h3>
      <p><%= summary.inventoryQuantity %></p>
      <span>Warehouse inventory count</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Department Portals</h2>
  <div class="portal-grid">
    <% portals.forEach((portal) => { %>
      <a class="portal-card" href="/portals/<%= portal.slug %>">
        <span class="eyebrow"><%= portal.eyebrow %></span>
        <h3><%= portal.title %></h3>
        <p><%= portal.summary %></p>
        <strong><%= portal.primaryMetric %></strong>
      </a>
    <% }) %>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="schema-note">
  <h2>Recommended Build Direction</h2>
  <p>The pasted item list can stay as a throwaway test, but the application shell is now oriented around your planned operational schema: employees, locations, lots, projects, units, technician assignments, inventory, and configurable statuses.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Use role-based access so management, tech, warehouse, and sales users each get the right default dashboard.</li>
    <li>Add event/history tables for unit status changes, inventory movements, sales reservations, and technician work logs so charts are based on auditable activity.</li>
    <li>Keep shared lookup values in config tables so statuses and dropdowns can change without code deployments.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<%- include('../partials/layout-end') %>
